Pope was startled and scared‚ and aster expressing his surprize to the Cardinals in somewhat unseemly language, he turned to the Monk‚ and said, ‘⁶ Brother, by St. Peter you shall not wait for my death, your petition is granted ;'' and before Pope Inno- cent again tasted food, he issued the Bull by which Archbishop Hubert was authorized to restore the Monastery.

Now as this statement is wholly inconsistent with the Bull, which is preserved textually and entire, we must either admit that the document is a forgery - and, at this period, the practice

of fabricating spurious Bulls prevailed exceedingly — or that

Matthew Paris, the Monk of St. Albans, was singularly deceived.
